stershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, Anglie","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Francie"},"da":{"25 January 1426–1466":"25. januar 1426–1466","1430–Male":"1430–Afdød","1454–Male":"1454–Afdød","1455–1497":"1455–1497","1426–1466":"1426–1466","1426":"1426","25 January 1426":"25. januar 1426","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1454":"1454","1497":"1497","1430":"1430","Wellington, Herefordshire, England":"Wellington, Herefordshire, England","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Frankrig"},"nl":{"25 January 1426–1466":"25 januari 1426–1466","1430–Male":"1430–Overleden","1454–Male":"1454–Overleden","1455–1497":"1455–1497","1426–1466":"1426–1466","1426":"1426","25 January 1426":"25 januari 1426","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1454":"1454","1497":"1497","1430":"1430","Wellington, Herefordshire, England":"Wellington, Herefordshire, England","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"25 January 1426–1466":"25 January 1426–1466","1430–Male":"1430–Deceased","1454–Male":"1454–Deceased","1455–1497":"1455–1497","1426–1466":"1426–1466","1426":"1426","25 January 1426":"25 January 1426","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1454":"1454","1497":"1497","1430":"1430","Wellington, Herefordshire, England":"Wellington, Herefordshire, England","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Walwyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish:","from the Middle English personal name <i>Wal(d)wine</i>, which is of ancient Germanic origin, from elements meaning ‘power’ + ‘friend’.","from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Walweyn</i>, <i>Walwain</i>. The central French form of this name is <i>Gawain</i> (see   Gavin  ). This name is found in the medieval Arthurian romances and is traditionally explained as an adaptation of the Welsh name <i>Gwalchmei</i>, perhaps meaning ‘hawk of the plain’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gavin","meanings":["Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Gábháin</b> or <b>Ó Gáibhín</b>, both of which are derived from diminutives of <i>gábhadh</i> ‘want’ or ‘danger’ (the second being the more likely meaning here).","Scottish and northern English: from the personal name <i>Gavin</i>, Scottish form of English <i>Gawain</i> and French   Gauvain  . The name was introduced into English from French versions of the Arthurian romances, where this name was borne by one of the knights of the Round Table, brother of Galahad and Mordred and a nephew of Arthur. It has been taken to be an adaptation of the Welsh name <i>Gwalchmei</i>, perhaps ‘hawk of the plain’.","Scottish: shortened form of   McGavin  , which is believed to be an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Gobhann</b> ‘son of the smith’."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":28,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen Walwyn was born on 25 January 1426, in Wellington, Herefordshire, England. She married Richard Monington in 1454, in Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1466, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 40."},"et":{"25 January 1426–1466":"25. jaanuar 1426–1466","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1454–Male":"1454–Surnud","1455–1497":"1455–1497","1426–1466":"1426–1466","1426":"1426","25 January 1426":"25. jaanuar 1426","1455":"1455","1466":"1466","1454":"1454","1497":"1497","1430":"1430","Wellington, Herefordshire, England":"Wellington, Herefordshire, England","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England":"Pauntley, Gloucestershire, England","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"25 January 1426–1466":"25. tammikuuta 1426–1466","1430–Male":"1430–Kuollut","1454–Male":"1454–Kuollut","1455–1497":"1455–1497","142